consent:
You are being asked to participate in a research study because we are interested in how adults (participants over

the age of 18) process social information.



Purpose:

The purpose of this research study is to help us understand how people form first impressions. In this research, we

are especially interested in how participants form impressions of other people based on their appearance. If looking at a computer screen for an extended period of time (approximately 30 minutes) is discomforting, or if repeated exposure to face stimuli is unsettling, you may not wish to participate in this study. Alternatively, you may want to participate in this research to help advance scientific knowledge of how impressions are formed.



Procedures:

If you agree to participate in this research study, we will ask you to do the following:

	You will be asked to complete a task that involved looking at faces and answering questions about them. The entire experiment will be completed on a computer and all of your responses will be recorded and saved using specialized software programs designed for psychology research.
	
		We may ask you questions like “what emotion is this person expressing” and your response will be recorded.
		The entire experiment will be conducted online.
	
	
	In addition, after the face perception task, you will be asked to complete two personality measures that allow us to know a little about your traits and backgrounds. You are welcome to skip any questions you don’t want to answer.
	We will also ask you to provide demographic information. This information is recorded only to ensure we are collecting a random and representative sample of study participants. You are welcome to skip any demographic questions.

For scientific reasons, this consent form does not include complete information about the purpose of this research. You will be fully debriefed following your participation in the research.



Time Commitment:

Your participation in this research study is expected to last for a total of 30 minutes.



Potential Risks or Discomforts:


	There are no known major risks associated with participation in this study. However, some of the questions the researchers ask you may be upsetting, or you may feel uncomfortable answering them. If you do not wish to answer a question, you may skip it and go to the next question. Should you feel uncomfortable at any time during the course of the experiment you can discontinue participation and still be compensated for your time. The risks are no greater than those you would experience in ordinary life.

Research Compensation:


	You will receive .5 credits toward your research requirement in exchange for participating in this study.



A full version of this consent form is attached here. Please download and review the full version. 



After reading the consent form, please indicate whether you consent to participate in this research study.
